{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Ez88jgDdciMKowgA8rrhcz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is healthy. Here's what was wrong and what I fixed:\n\n**Root cause:** `app-user` had no **configure** permission on the `/app` vhost. In RabbitMQ, declaring (creating) a queue requires configure permission — write permission alone only allows publishing to existing queues. The permissions were:\n\n```\nuser      configure   write   read\napp-user  (empty)     .*      .*\n```\n\n**Fix:** Granted `app-user` full permissions on `/app`:\n```bash\nrabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user '.*' '.*' '.*'\n```\n\n**Verified state:**\n- `app-producer` is Running with 0 restarts (no CrashLoop)\n- `/app` vhost contains `app-queue` of type `classic` with 70 messages (and growing — the producer is actively publishing)\n- All 3 RabbitMQ nodes (`rabbitmq-0/1/2`) are running and in cluster"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":357,"cache_read_input_tokens":32824,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":357},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"95377335-6350-4575-99a0-de321029324a","uuid":"45868abc-6131-4601-98ba-fe5c5a16e6dd","request_id":"req_011CcbnyBMEf8gEKEDict2gy"}
